Long before Turkey intended to join the European Union, European powers were burning with a desire to penetrate deep into the Turkish backdrop.
On the eastern side of the Bosporus, perhaps just 20 steps from the European border, stands one of the greatest relics of the failed imperial quest.
Hydarpasha railway station was designed by two German architects, Otto Ritter and Helmut Conu, in the Neo-Renaissance style.
